  "articleSummary": "This article recounts the author's upgrade of an 8-year-old Gatsby v1 blog to a modern static site, primarily using Astro. The core thesis is that Astro's simplicity and lack of framework/cloud bias made it the ideal choice for meeting requirements like sub-1-second load times, code highlighting, comments, and search. Key technologies include Astro, Tailwind CSS (with noted regrets), Pagefind for search, and Utterances for comments. The tone is a reflective tutorial/analysis aimed at developers evaluating static site generators or planning a similar migration. The author frames the process as a \"journey\" and positions Astro as the \"cornerstone\" of the upgrade.",
